# No Auto-Installing Packages

Never install packages (pip, npm, apt, etc.) without explicitly asking the user for permission first. The user manages their own .venv and dependencies.

- Always ask before running `pip install`, `apt install`, or any package manager command.
- If a task requires a new dependency, tell the user what is needed and why, then wait for approval.
- Use Cursor's tool allowlist to restrict shell commands when possible.
